This paper proposes a new loss function for semantic segmentation that incorporates structural information of objects in an image. This is a common problem in computer vision, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing the correlation between the ground truth map and the predicted map, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The method also involves using a similarity index to quantify the structural similarity between two images, which is a common technique in image processing and computer vision (cs.AI, cs.MM). Finally, the method involves minimizing a loss function, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (cs.NE).
